439, \"to\": 454}, {\"ngram\": \"comeback campaigns\", \"from\": 458, \"to\": 476}, {\"ngram\": \"Team USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s most prominent athletes\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 525}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simone Biles, Sunisa Lee, Sha\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Carri Richardson.\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 543, \"end\": 553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sunisa Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 567, \"end\": 577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.733131325292241e-33, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Simone Biles\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 541}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two gymnasts and a sprinter, each of whom has held a central role in our domestic success at the Olympics thus far (the U.S. currently leads with the most gold medals won) and in drawing a global audience to their screens.\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 801, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Two gymnasts\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 591}, {\"ngram\": \"a sprinter\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 606}, {\"ngram\": \"a central role\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 644}, {\"ngram\": \"our domestic success\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 668}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 684}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 695, \"to\": 703}, {\"ngram\": \"the most gold medals\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 745}, {\"ngram\": \"a global audience\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 783}, {\"ngram\": \"their screens\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 800}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For all that distinguishes them athletically, there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s one commonality that Biles, Lee and Richardson share in earnest \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 their redemption tour.\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 948, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 886, \"end\": 889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.9675411848907076e-12, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 894, \"end\": 904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.733131325292241e-33, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 884}, {\"ngram\": \"earnest \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 925}, {\"ngram\": \"their redemption tour\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 947}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before they were Olympians, they were Simone, Sunisa and Sha\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Carri.\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 1019, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 976}, {\"ngram\": \"Simone\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 994}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunisa\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1002}, {\"ngram\": \"Sha\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Carri\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1018}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Currently, each of these women is at the height of their physical performance, further cementing themselves as exemplars of their respective sports through their Olympic efforts.\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1199, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these women\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1051}, {\"ngram\": \"the height\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1068}, {\"ngram\": \"their physical performance\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1098}, {\"ngram\": \"exemplars\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1141}, {\"ngram\": \"their respective sports\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1168}, {\"ngram\": \"their Olympic efforts\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1198}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But how do we conceptualize them outside of this mold?\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1254, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this mold\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1253}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the aerials, the back handsprings, the 100-meter dashes and relay handoffs, these seemingly otherworldly talents are still regular people.\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1400, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the aerials\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"the back handsprings\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1295}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100-meter dashes\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1317}, {\"ngram\": \"relay handoffs\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1336}, {\"ngram\": \"these seemingly otherworldly talents\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1374}, {\"ngram\": \"regular people\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And regular people, as anyone can attest, are saddled with issues outside of their professional lives that still directly affect them.\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1535, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"regular people\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1419}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1430}, {\"ngram\": \"issues\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1466}, {\"ngram\": \"their professional lives\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1502}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We can look then, to this trio's comeback stories and successes in Paris as a reminder that we should view people holistically, not merely through the lens of their chosen disciplines or what they most excel at.\\u00c2 Related In Salon's recentinterviewfor the Netflix documentary, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSimone Biles: Rising,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d director Katie Walsh shared that Biles felt it was pivotal to \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cgive people a window into her entire self.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe all see her on the floor as the G.O.A.T.\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 2000, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1603, \"end\": 1608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9680431784347923e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1762, \"end\": 1767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.884947073541944e-47, \"text\": \"Salon\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\"}, {\"begin\": 1851, \"end\": 1862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Walsh_(jockey)\", \"score\": 0.7867161401851925, \"rank\": 0.27110582639697917, \"text\": \"Katie Walsh\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Walsh_(jockey)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Walsh_(jockey)\"}, {\"begin\": 1992, \"end\": 2000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/G.O.A.T._(LL_Cool_J_album)\", \"score\": 0.9696969688265445, \"rank\": 0.031250000000001485, \"text\": \"G.O.A.T.\", \"types\": [\"Q482994\", \"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/G.O.A.T._(LL_Cool_J_album)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/G.O.A.T._(LL_Cool_J_album)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this trio's comeback stories\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1585}, {\"ngram\": \"successes\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1599}, {\"ngram\": \"a reminder\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1622}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1649}, {\"ngram\": \"the lens\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1691}, {\"ngram\": \"their chosen disciplines\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1719}, {\"ngram\": \"the Netflix documentary\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1810}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSimone Biles\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1827}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1878}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cgive people\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 1916}, {\"ngram\": \"her entire self.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 1956}, {\"ngram\": \"the floor\", \"from\": 1972, \"to\": 1981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"and the greatest ever.\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But we all do not get to see and have the privilege of getting to know Simone, the human being,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Walsh said.\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2134, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the privilege\", \"from\": 2062, \"to\": 2075}, {\"ngram\": \"Simone\", \"from\": 2095, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"the human being\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2118}, {\"ngram\": \"Walsh\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2128}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAnd I know for her, she wants to be looked at and viewed as a full human and not just this amazing gymnast you have come to really expect to be perfect at all times.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Given that Biles, who recently becamethe most decorated American gymnast of all time, is widely regarded as an uncontested talent in the sport, a comeback is not necessarily something that fans might have expected of her.\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2364, \"end\": 2372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.512603369096301e-17, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a full human\", \"from\": 2198, \"to\": 2210}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2323}, {\"ngram\": \"all time\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2391}, {\"ngram\": \"an uncontested talent\", \"from\": 2415, \"to\": 2436}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2449}, {\"ngram\": \"a comeback\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2461}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2490}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 2496, \"to\": 2500}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What would she have to return to if she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s already at the top?\", \"from\": 2530, \"to\": 2593, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2592}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sentiments \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 and the documentary more broadly \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 follow a debilitating era in the Biles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 history in gymnastics.\", \"from\": 2595, \"to\": 2721, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Walsh\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 2595, \"to\": 2604}, {\"ngram\": \"the documentary\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2639}, {\"ngram\": \"a debilitating era\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2682}, {\"ngram\": \"the Biles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 history\", \"from\": 2686, \"to\": 2706}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnastics\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2720}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After suffering a bout of the\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009ctwisties,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\\u00c2 a disorienting sensation that unmoored Biles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 body from her mind in Tokyo, she elected to withdraw from the Games.\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2838, \"end\": 2843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999389081830375, \"rank\": 6.109554922238248e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bout\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2744}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\\u00c2\", \"from\": 2763, \"to\": 2767}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 body\", \"from\": 2807, \"to\": 2820}, {\"ngram\": \"her mind\", \"from\": 2826, \"to\": 2834}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 2883}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI have to focus on my mental health,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Biles said at the time,per the BBC.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t trust myself as much anymore.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Simone Biles Rising (Netflix)Evidently, neither did a number of others.\", \"from\": 2885, \"to\": 3081, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my mental health\", \"from\": 2907, \"to\": 2923}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 2933}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 2942, \"to\": 2950}, {\"ngram\": \"a number\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3069}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 3073, \"to\": 3079}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rather than being lauded for her bravery (and numerous medals from the Rio Games in 2016), her decision was widely panned by online critics who scrutinized her \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cabandonment\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d of her teammates.\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3277, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her bravery\", \"from\": 3111, \"to\": 3122}, {\"ngram\": \"numerous medals\", \"from\": 3128, \"to\": 3143}, {\"ngram\": \"the Rio Games\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3162}, {\"ngram\": \"her decision\", \"from\": 3173, \"to\": 3185}, {\"ngram\": \"online critics\", \"from\": 3207, \"to\": 3221}, {\"ngram\": \"her \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cabandonment\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 3238, \"to\": 3259}, {\"ngram\": \"her teammates\", \"from\": 3263, \"to\": 3276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Media mudslinging abounded on various social media platforms.\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3339, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Media mudslinging\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3295}, {\"ngram\": \"various social media platforms\", \"from\": 3308, \"to\": 3338}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Journalist Tim Constantine swiftly authored anop-ed for The Washington Timestitled, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSimone Biles is no hero.\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3400, \"end\": 3410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"score\": 0.9999725639043667, \"rank\": 2.7436848333146643e-05, \"text\": \"Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Journalist Tim Constantine\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3366}, {\"ngram\": \"anop-ed\", \"from\": 3384, \"to\": 3391}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSimone Biles\", \"from\": 3424, \"to\": 3439}, {\"ngram\": \"no hero\", \"from\": 3443, \"to\": 3450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is a quitter.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Coupled with her 2021testimonybefore the U.S. Senate regarding sexual abuse she and other members of USA Gymnastics endured by former team doctor, Larry Nassar, Biles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 mental health quickly deteriorated.\\u00c2 Three years later, Biles has flipped the script on the haters, outperforming even herself with three gold medals \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 all-around team, all-around individual, and vault \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 and one silver \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 for the floor event \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 to add to her collection.\", \"from\": 3452, \"to\": 3920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3519, \"end\": 3525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Senate\", \"score\": 0.999988180941542, \"rank\": 1.1819132216807521e-05, \"text\": \"Senate\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Senate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Senate\"}, {\"begin\": 3574, \"end\": 3588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.110267697788242e-12, \"text\": \"USA Gymnastics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics\"}, {\"begin\": 3620, \"end\": 3632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics_sex_abuse_scandal\", \"score\": 0.9999556675034051, \"rank\": 4.4334461899972995e-05, \"text\": \"Larry Nassar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics_sex_abuse_scandal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics_sex_abuse_scandal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her 2021testimonybefore\", \"from\": 3486, \"to\": 3509}, {\"ngram\": \"sexual abuse\", \"from\": 3536, \"to\": 3548}, {\"ngram\": \"other members\", \"from\": 3557, \"to\": 3570}, {\"ngram\": \"former team doctor\", \"from\": 3600, \"to\": 3618}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 mental health\", \"from\": 3634, \"to\": 3656}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 3678, \"to\": 3679}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 3699, \"to\": 3704}, {\"ngram\": \"the script\", \"from\": 3717, \"to\": 3727}, {\"ngram\": \"the haters\", \"from\": 3731, \"to\": 3741}, {\"ngram\": \"even herself\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3769}, {\"ngram\": \"three gold medals\", \"from\": 3775, \"to\": 3792}, {\"ngram\": \"all-around individual\", \"from\": 3814, \"to\": 3835}, {\"ngram\": \"one silver\", \"from\": 3855, \"to\": 3865}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094\", \"from\": 3866, \"to\": 3869}, {\"ngram\": \"the floor event\", \"from\": 3874, \"to\": 3889}, {\"ngram\": \"her collection\", \"from\": 3904, \"to\": 3918}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBeing in a good mental spot, seeing my therapist every Thursday is kind of religious for me.\", \"from\": 3921, \"to\": 4016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a good mental spot\", \"from\": 3933, \"to\": 3951}, {\"ngram\": \"my therapist\", \"from\": 3960, \"to\": 3972}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s why I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m here today,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the phenomtold NBCin a June interview, openly attributing consistent mental care to her sparkling return.\\u00c2 Many Americans can and should look to Biles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 embracement of mental health services for inspiration.\", \"from\": 4017, \"to\": 4263, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m\", \"from\": 4033, \"to\": 4038}, {\"ngram\": \"the phenomtold NBCin\", \"from\": 4054, \"to\": 4074}, {\"ngram\": \"a June interview\", \"from\": 4075, \"to\": 4091}, {\"ngram\": \"consistent mental care\", \"from\": 4112, \"to\": 4134}, {\"ngram\": \"her sparkling return\", \"from\": 4138, \"to\": 4158}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 4159, \"to\": 4160}, {\"ngram\": \"Many Americans\", \"from\": 4161, \"to\": 4175}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 embracement\", \"from\": 4199, \"to\": 4219}, {\"ngram\": \"mental health services\", \"from\": 4223, \"to\": 4245}, {\"ngram\": \"inspiration\", \"from\": 4250, \"to\": 4261}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A 2021reportfrom the Mental Health Million Project found that 45 percent of individuals in the U.S. suffering from a clinical mental problem do not seek help.\", \"from\": 4264, \"to\": 4422, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Mental Health Million Project\", \"from\": 4281, \"to\": 4314}, {\"ngram\": \"45 percent\", \"from\": 4326, \"to\": 4336}, {\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 4340, \"to\": 4351}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 4355, \"to\": 4363}, {\"ngram\": \"a clinical mental problem\", \"from\": 4379, \"to\": 4404}, {\"ngram\": \"help\", \"from\": 4417, \"to\": 4421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the reasons behind why people forgo treatment are varied and often subjective, America\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s cultural dismissal of therapy and general obstinance about prioritizing mental health gives credence to the intense backlash Biles faced post-Tokyo.\\u00c2 For Lee, the issues plaguing her physical health found a nexus with her mental state.\", \"from\": 4423, \"to\": 4756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4675, \"end\": 4678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.9675411848907076e-12, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the reasons\", \"from\": 4429, \"to\": 4440}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 4452, \"to\": 4458}, {\"ngram\": \"treatment\", \"from\": 4465, \"to\": 4474}, {\"ngram\": \"varied and often subjective, America\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s cultural dismissal\", \"from\": 4479, \"to\": 4538}, {\"ngram\": \"therapy\", \"from\": 4542, \"to\": 4549}, {\"ngram\": \"general obstinance\", \"from\": 4554, \"to\": 4572}, {\"ngram\": \"mental health\", \"from\": 4592, \"to\": 4605}, {\"ngram\": \"credence\", \"from\": 4612, \"to\": 4620}, {\"ngram\": \"the intense backlash\", \"from\": 4624, \"to\": 4644}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 4645, \"to\": 4650}, {\"ngram\": \"post\", \"from\": 4657, \"to\": 4661}, {\"ngram\": \"Tokyo\", \"from\": 4662, \"to\": 4667}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 4668, \"to\": 4669}, {\"ngram\": \"the issues\", \"from\": 4679, \"to\": 4689}, {\"ngram\": \"her physical health\", \"from\": 4699, \"to\": 4718}, {\"ngram\": \"a nexus\", \"from\": 4725, \"to\": 4732}, {\"ngram\": \"her mental state\", \"from\": 4738, \"to\": 4754}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her path to the Paris Games was stymied by a diagnosis in 2022.\", \"from\": 4757, \"to\": 4820, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her path\", \"from\": 4757, \"to\": 4765}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 4769, \"to\": 4784}, {\"ngram\": \"a diagnosis\", \"from\": 4800, \"to\": 4811}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A chronic, incurable kidney disease left her with a litany of adverse symptoms.\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t something like I can just take a pill and be better; I was going to have to deal with this my whole life,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Lee, who earned agold medalin the individual all-around in Tokyo, told the New York Times in aninterviewpublished last month.\", \"from\": 4821, \"to\": 5152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5027, \"end\": 5030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.9675411848907076e-12, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 5086, \"end\": 5091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999389081830375, \"rank\": 6.109554922238248e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 5102, \"end\": 5110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.404326618779901e-13, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A chronic, incurable kidney disease\", \"from\": 4821, \"to\": 4856}, {\"ngram\": \"a litany\", \"from\": 4871, \"to\": 4879}, {\"ngram\": \"adverse symptoms\", \"from\": 4883, \"to\": 4899}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\", \"from\": 4900, \"to\": 4907}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 4917, \"to\": 4926}, {\"ngram\": \"a pill\", \"from\": 4948, \"to\": 4954}, {\"ngram\": \"my whole life\", \"from\": 5008, \"to\": 5021}, {\"ngram\": \"agold\", \"from\": 5042, \"to\": 5047}, {\"ngram\": \"medalin\", \"from\": 5048, \"to\": 5055}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Lee hasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t publicly shared the specifics of her condition \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cbecause it may change as her medical team learns more about her illness,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009das noted by TODAY,abnormal swelling, hot flashes, cold spells and headaches forced her to modify her training and begin intensive physical therapy.\", \"from\": 5154, \"to\": 5445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5160, \"end\": 5163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.9675411848907076e-12, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the specifics\", \"from\": 5189, \"to\": 5202}, {\"ngram\": \"her condition\", \"from\": 5206, \"to\": 5219}, {\"ngram\": \"her medical team\", \"from\": 5248, \"to\": 5264}, {\"ngram\": \"her illness\", \"from\": 5283, \"to\": 5294}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009das\", \"from\": 5295, \"to\": 5300}, {\"ngram\": \"TODAY\", \"from\": 5310, \"to\": 5315}, {\"ngram\": \"abnormal swelling\", \"from\": 5316, \"to\": 5333}, {\"ngram\": \"hot flashes\", \"from\": 5335, \"to\": 5346}, {\"ngram\": \"cold spells\", \"from\": 5348, \"to\": 5359}, {\"ngram\": \"headaches\", \"from\": 5364, \"to\": 5373}, {\"ngram\": \"her training\", \"from\": 5395, \"to\": 5407}, {\"ngram\": \"intensive physical therapy\", \"from\": 5418, \"to\": 5444}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was an ironic situation in the fullest sense \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 her physical prowess, what her worth had hinged upon as far as society was concerned, was at bitter odds with her body.\", \"from\": 5446, \"to\": 5617, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an ironic situation\", \"from\": 5453, \"to\": 5472}, {\"ngram\": \"the fullest sense\", \"from\": 5476, \"to\": 5493}, {\"ngram\": \"her physical prowess\", \"from\": 5498, \"to\": 5518}, {\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 5561, \"to\": 5568}, {\"ngram\": \"bitter odds\", \"from\": 5591, \"to\": 5602}, {\"ngram\": \"her body\", \"from\": 5608, \"to\": 5616}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI was like, who is this person looking back at me?\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Lee told The Times.\", \"from\": 5619, \"to\": 5695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5676, \"end\": 5679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.9675411848907076e-12, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 5685, \"end\": 5694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.34910730478481e-17, \"text\": \"The Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\", \"from\": 5619, \"to\": 5623}, {\"ngram\": \"this person\", \"from\": 5641, \"to\": 5652}, {\"ngram\": \"me?\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 5669, \"to\": 5675}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt was so scary.\", \"from\": 5696, \"to\": 5715, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\", \"from\": 5696, \"to\": 5701}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t know it then, but the old Suni was gone.\", \"from\": 5716, \"to\": 5767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5753, \"end\": 5757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suni\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.599690478839194e-17, \"text\": \"Suni\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suni\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suni\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And she would never be back.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Sunisa Lee of Team United States on Balance Beam competes during the women's Artistic Gymnastics All-Around Final on day six of the Olympic Games Paris 2024 at Bercy Arena on August 01, 2024 in Paris, France.\", \"from\": 5768, \"to\": 6009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5801, \"end\": 5811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sunisa Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 5820, \"end\": 5833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999890214896, \"rank\": 1.097838417425011e-08, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 5887, \"end\": 5897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.125475327332478e-13, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\"}, {\"begin\": 5995, \"end\": 6000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9680431784347923e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6002, \"end\": 6008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999809911078, \"rank\": 1.882509179597427e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"day\", \"from\": 5917, \"to\": 5920}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games Paris\", \"from\": 5928, \"to\": 5951}, {\"ngram\": \"Bercy Arena\", \"from\": 5960, \"to\": 5971}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 5975, \"to\": 5981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Stefan Matzke \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 sampics/Getty Images) Champions are made, not by pandering to the noise, but by believing in the fullest version of oneself.\", \"from\": 6010, \"to\": 6154, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sampics\", \"from\": 6029, \"to\": 6036}, {\"ngram\": \"Getty Images\", \"from\": 6037, \"to\": 6049}, {\"ngram\": \"the noise\", \"from\": 6091, \"to\": 6100}, {\"ngram\": \"the fullest version\", \"from\": 6122, \"to\": 6141}, {\"ngram\": \"oneself\", \"from\": 6145, \"to\": 6152}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s case is only one instance of how invisible illnesses remain an unaddressed issue in athletics; oftentimes, interest and sympathy are only assigned to ailments that can be perceived outwardly.\", \"from\": 6156, \"to\": 6355, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Lee\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s case\", \"from\": 6156, \"to\": 6168}, {\"ngram\": \"only one instance\", \"from\": 6172, \"to\": 6189}, {\"ngram\": \"how invisible illnesses\", \"from\": 6193, \"to\": 6216}, {\"ngram\": \"an unaddressed issue\", \"from\": 6224, \"to\": 6244}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 6248, \"to\": 6257}, {\"ngram\": \"oftentimes\", \"from\": 6259, \"to\": 6269}, {\"ngram\": \"interest\", \"from\": 6271, \"to\": 6279}, {\"ngram\": \"sympathy\", \"from\": 6284, \"to\": 6292}, {\"ngram\": \"ailments\", \"from\": 6314, \"to\": 6322}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a 2023column for Slate,\\u00c2 Fortesa Latifi writes, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cChronic illness forces you to make a choice: look at your body differently, as something that is imperfect, or spend your entire life mourning what has been left behind in the land of health.\", \"from\": 6356, \"to\": 6601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6376, \"end\": 6381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slate\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.651089266812525e-37, \"text\": \"Slate\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slate\"}, {\"begin\": 6384, \"end\": 6391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fortesa_Hoti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fortesa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q33999\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fortesa_Hoti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fortesa_Hoti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a 2023column\", \"from\": 6359, \"to\": 6371}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cChronic illness\", \"from\": 6407, \"to\": 6425}, {\"ngram\": \"a choice\", \"from\": 6445, \"to\": 6453}, {\"ngram\": \"your body\", \"from\": 6463, \"to\": 6472}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 6489, \"to\": 6498}, {\"ngram\": \"your entire life\", \"from\": 6527, \"to\": 6543}, {\"ngram\": \"the land\", \"from\": 6582, \"to\": 6590}, {\"ngram\": \"health\", \"from\": 6594, \"to\": 6600}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For chronically ill athletes, it can be a tightrope walk to figure out how to push their bodies while respecting the limits of their diseases.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Oftentimes, there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a chasmic dissonance between the urge to fulfill societal expectations of the quintessential athlete and what can actually be accomplished while one\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s health flounders.\", \"from\": 6602, \"to\": 6940, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"chronically ill athletes\", \"from\": 6606, \"to\": 6630}, {\"ngram\": \"their bodies\", \"from\": 6685, \"to\": 6697}, {\"ngram\": \"the limits\", \"from\": 6715, \"to\": 6725}, {\"ngram\": \"their diseases.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Oftentimes\", \"from\": 6729, \"to\": 6758}, {\"ngram\": \"there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 6760, \"to\": 6769}, {\"ngram\": \"the urge\", \"from\": 6799, \"to\": 6807}, {\"ngram\": \"societal expectations\", \"from\": 6819, \"to\": 6840}, {\"ngram\": \"the quintessential athlete\", \"from\": 6844, \"to\": 6870}, {\"ngram\": \"health flounders\", \"from\": 6923, \"to\": 6939}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As alongtime competitive runnerand chronically ill person, this is an experience I can speak to directly.\", \"from\": 6941, \"to\": 7046, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an experience\", \"from\": 7008, \"to\": 7021}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee however remained undeterred by her illness and summoned the gumption and self-confidence to return to the mat after a brief hiatus, brushing aside the narrowly construed frameworks of athleticism.\", \"from\": 7048, \"to\": 7248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7048, \"end\": 7051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.9675411848907076e-12, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her illness\", \"from\": 7083, \"to\": 7094}, {\"ngram\": \"the gumption\", \"from\": 7108, \"to\": 7120}, {\"ngram\": \"self-confidence\", \"from\": 7125, \"to\": 7140}, {\"ngram\": \"the mat\", \"from\": 7154, \"to\": 7161}, {\"ngram\": \"a brief hiatus\", \"from\": 7168, \"to\": 7182}, {\"ngram\": \"the narrowly construed frameworks\", \"from\": 7199, \"to\": 7232}, {\"ngram\": \"athleticism\", \"from\": 7236, \"to\": 7247}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThis comeback was so much more than my return to elite gymnastics,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she wrote in a 2023 Instagrampost.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt was me proving to myself that I can overcome hard things, and to hopefully inspire others to never let life\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s setbacks stop you from going after your dreams.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d https://www.instagram.com/p/CvnNv1TO648/?igshid=NTY1MGJiNDNiYw%3D%3D&img_index=1 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cMy doctor was telling me he didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d be able to do gymnastics ever again,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Lee shared with TODAY.\", \"from\": 7249, \"to\": 7722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7700, \"end\": 7703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.9675411848907076e-12, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThis comeback\", \"from\": 7249, \"to\": 7265}, {\"ngram\": \"my return\", \"from\": 7288, \"to\": 7297}, {\"ngram\": \"elite gymnastics\", \"from\": 7301, \"to\": 7317}, {\"ngram\": \"Instagrampost.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\", \"from\": 7342, \"to\": 7361}, {\"ngram\": \"hard things\", \"from\": 7407, \"to\": 7418}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 7445, \"to\": 7451}, {\"ngram\": \"life\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 7465, \"to\": 7473}, {\"ngram\": \"setbacks\", \"from\": 7474, \"to\": 7482}, {\"ngram\": \"your dreams.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 7509, \"to\": 7524}, {\"ngram\": \"https://www.instagram.com/p/CvnNv1TO648/?igshid=NTY1MGJiNDNiYw%3D%3D&img_index=1 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cMy doctor\", \"from\": 7525, \"to\": 7618}, {\"ngram\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d\", \"from\": 7652, \"to\": 7657}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnastics\", \"from\": 7672, \"to\": 7682}, {\"ngram\": \"TODAY\", \"from\": 7714, \"to\": 7719}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSo to even be here is an accomplishment in itself.\", \"from\": 7723, \"to\": 7776, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an accomplishment\", \"from\": 7748, \"to\": 7765}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m super proud of myself.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Then comes Richardson, the sprinting dynamo who saw her first shot at the Olympics dashed after testing positive for marijuana, leading to a 30-day suspension that saw her barred from Tokyo despite winning the 100-meter event at the trials.\", \"from\": 7777, \"to\": 8054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7825, \"end\": 7835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.733131325292241e-33, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 7998, \"end\": 8003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999389081830375, \"rank\": 6.109554922238248e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m\", \"from\": 7781, \"to\": 7786}, {\"ngram\": \"myself.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 7802, \"to\": 7812}, {\"ngram\": \"the sprinting dynamo\", \"from\": 7836, \"to\": 7856}, {\"ngram\": \"her first shot\", \"from\": 7865, \"to\": 7879}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 7883, \"to\": 7895}, {\"ngram\": \"marijuana\", \"from\": 7930, \"to\": 7939}, {\"ngram\": \"a 30-day suspension\", \"from\": 7952, \"to\": 7971}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100-meter event\", \"from\": 8019, \"to\": 8038}, {\"ngram\": \"the trials\", \"from\": 8042, \"to\": 8052}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But to hear it in her own words, it was a\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cnerve triggering\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d event that Richardson said sent her spiraling.Speaking to NBCaround the time of her suspension, Richardson claimed she had used drugs to cope with learning of the death of her biological mother.\", \"from\": 8055, \"to\": 8316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8133, \"end\": 8143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.733131325292241e-33, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 8218, \"end\": 8228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.733131325292241e-33, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", 